cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CE, cs.HC, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with explaining the predictions of a stateful dynamical model in a clinical setting, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The goal is to alert a clinician when a patient's risk of deterioration rises, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and potentially complex events (cs.SI). Finally, the paper also discusses experimental evaluation of different explanation methods, which falls under computational engineering (cs.CE).
